      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Seven days shalt thou make an atonement",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". All the ceremonial was to be repeated seven times, not only the atonement for the altar (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). An altar most holy. Literally, \"holiness of holinesses,\" as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 40:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Whatever toucheth the altar shall be holy. Rather, \"must be holy.\" Nothing that is not holy must touch it (Kalisch).  ",
